# NestHop: System Architecture & Technical Documentation

This technical document outlines the engineering blueprint, system architecture, and core workflows for NestHop—a hyper-focused full-stack web and mobile marketplace connecting landlords/caretakers with prospective tenants.

---

## 1. System Architecture Overview

NestHop utilizes a decoupled **MERN Stack** architecture designed to support a web interface (React/Vite) and real-time communication protocols concurrently.

```
┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                   NestHop Client                       │
│     (React + TypeScript + Tailwind v4 + Vite)          │
└───────────┬────────────────────────────▲───────────────┘
            │ HTTP / REST                │ WebSockets
            │ Requests                   │ (Socket.io-client)
┌───────────▼────────────────────────────┴───────────────┐
│                   NestHop Server                       │
│        (Node.js + Express + Socket.io)                 │
└───────────┬────────────────────────────────────────────┘
            │ Mongoose ODM
┌───────────▼────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                  Database Layer                        │
│                 (MongoDB Atlas)                        │
└────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

```

