## 3. Database Schema Blueprint

```
                          ┌──────────────────────┐
                          │         User         │
                          └──────────┬───────────┘
                                     │ 1
                                     │
                                     │ 1..*
                          ┌──────────▼───────────┐
                          │       Listing        │
                          └──────────┬───────────┘
                                     │ 1
                                     │
                                     │ 0..*
                          ┌──────────▼───────────┐
                          │    SupportTicket     │
                          └──────────────────────┘

```

### User Schema

Stores core demographic profiles and role-based permissions.

* `_id`: ObjectId
* `contactIdentifier`: String (Unique email or phone number)
* `role`: String (`'tenant'`, `'landlord'`, `'admin'`)
* `isVerified`: Boolean
* `isBanned`: Boolean

### Listing Schema

Maintains structural definitions and location arrays for properties.

* `_id`: ObjectId
* `creatorId`: ObjectId (References User)
* `title`: String
* `houseType`: String (`'single room'`, `'1 bedroom'`, etc.)
* `locationName`: String
* `coordinates`: `{ lat: Number, lng: Number }`
* `images`: Array of Strings (Cloud storage asset URLs)
* `sideNotes`: String

